Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at a meeting in the Vice President's Ceremonial Office in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. She thanked members of the Cabinet for their work and discussed the administration's commitment to improving the condition of workers and increasing union density. The administration has launched a task force to empower workers and increase union membership by leveraging executive authority. The task force will release a report on October 23rd with proposals to make it easier for workers to organize, use existing authorities, and impact every sector of employment. The Vice President also emphasized the importance of passing the PRO Act. Secretary of Labor Marty Walsh also spoke, expressing gratitude for the leadership and vision of the Vice President and discussing the impact of the task force's work on working people and the middle class. The Vice President later commented on the need to address the debt limit and pay the country's bills.